v1.0.0

- [DONE] store config data
  - all whitelisted config (board + channels) is one JSON object published at
    electrical.frothfet.config.{board} (see buildConfig)
  - board fields at top level; enabled channels nested under `channels`, keyed by slug
  - config path is always per-board; under 'none' it falls back to boardname (see getConfigBoardPath)
  - whitelists: plugin.boardConfigFields, plugin.channelConfigFields
  - secrets (wifi/mqtt/auth pass, certs) and trivia (boot log, melodies) are excluded by the whitelist
- control PUT routing under the "none" path scheme:
  - all boards register a handler on the shared electrical.frothfet.control path
  - a PUT is ambiguous about which board's websocket receives it (each handler
    forwards to its own board)
  - decide how to route: by board id/uuid in the payload, or some other scheme
- n2k digital switching
  - figure out what plugin can go from signalk -> n2k for digital switching
  - find out what format it prefers for data
  - add an option to also publish to the n2k digital switching paths
  - add plugin as recommended
- update readme
- screenshots
- update changelog